Ubuntu 10.10
1. Synaptic Package Manager: ssh (with openssh-server)
2. NTFS Configuration Tool
	2.1 Ubuntu Software Center: NTFS Configuration Tool
	2.2 In terminal, "sudo apt-get install hal"
3. Chinese Input
	3.1 System - Administration - Language Support: Install Chinese and enable ibus
	3.2 System - Preferences - Keyboard Input Methods: Add Pinyin
4. Ubuntu Software Center: rar
5. Java
	5.1 Download jdk: http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/index.html
	5.2 Follow instructions: http://sites.google.com/site/easylinuxtipsproject/java
		cd /opt
		sudo mkdir java
		cd java
		sudo mkdir 64
		sudo mv ~/Downloads/jdk-6u22-linux-x64.bin /opt/java/64
		sudo chmod 755 /opt/java/64/jdk-6u22-linux-x64.bin
		cd /opt/java/64
		sudo ./jdk-6u22-linux-x64.bin
		sudo update-alternatives --install "/usr/bin/java" "java" "/opt/java/64/jdk1.6.0_22/jre/bin/java" 1
		sudo update-alternatives --set java /opt/java/64/jdk1.6.0_22/jre/bin/java
		mkdir ~/.mozilla/plugins
		sudo apt-get remove icedtea6-plugin
		rm ~/.mozilla/plugins/libnpjp2.so
		ln -s /opt/java/64/jdk1.6.0_22/jre/lib/amd64/libnpjp2.so ~/.mozilla/plugins/
6. Matlab
	6.1 Download matlab from drexel and extract
	6.2 Follow instructions: https://help.ubuntu.com/community/MATLAB/R2009b
		sudo mkdir /usr/local/MATLAB/
		sudo mkdir /usr/local/MATLAB/R2010b
		cd /usr/local/MATLAB/R2010b
		sudo sh /home/zexi/Downloads/Matlab2010b_Linux64/install
	Get an icon
		sudo wget http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/21/Matlab_Logo.png -O /usr/share/icons/matlab.png
	After installation, create an launcher on the desktop with command "matlab -desktop", and double click it to start
		sudo chown -R ${USER}:${USER} ~/.matlab
		cd usr/local/MATLAB/R2010b/toolbox/local
		sudo chmod 777 pathdef.m
7. Open terminals anywhere
	7.1 Synaptic Package Manager: nautilus-open-terminal
	7.2 In terminal, "killall -9 nautilus"
8. Maple
	8.1 Synaptic Package Manager: lsb-core (with alien, bsd-mailx, build-essential...)
	8.2 sudo chmod 755 Maple14_64bit.bin
	8.3 Run ./Maple14_64bit.bin
9. Netbeans:
	9.1 sudo chmod 755 netbeans-6.9.1-ml-linux.sh
	9.2 Run netbeans-6.9.1-ml-linux.sh

Restart computer

