18. Creates an undecorated window with black background that prevents the mouse from entering its "visible" area
	18.1 Synaptic Package Manager: xserver-xorg-dev
	18.2 Download code from http://launchpadlibrarian.net/58365197/XCreateMouseVoid.c
	18.3 Create a NetBeans C project
	18.4 Add XCreateMouseVoid.c as a source file in this project
	18.5 Go to project properties (right click project name) -> Linker -> Libraries -> Add Library -> Dynamic Library (.so) -> libX11.so
	18.6 Build and obtain the executables from NetBeansProjects/XCreateMouseVoid/dist/Debug/GNU-Linux-x86
19. Blender
	19.1 Ubuntu Software Center: Blender (Windowed)

Restart computer

20. Wine (version 1.2.1)
	20.1 Remove previous versions
		sudo apt-get remove wine
		rm -rf $HOME/.wine
		rm -f $HOME/.config/menus/applications-merged/wine*
		rm -rf $HOME/.local/share/applications/wine
		rm -f $HOME/.local/share/desktop-directories/wine*
		rm -f $HOME/.local/share/icons/????_*.xpm
	20.2 Install wine
		sudo apt-get install wine
	20.3 Deleting old Icons that WINE leaves behind
		When 'uninstaling' a program though WINE it still leaves the folder list and icons in the WINE menu
		In order to delete them, go to ~/.local/share/applications/wine/
21. Geomagic 11
	21.1 Find StudioInstaller_32.exe, right click it, Open with Wine Window Program Loader
	22.2 After installation, go to /home/zexi/.wine/drive_c/Program Files/Geomagic/Geomagic Studio 11, open in terminal
	22.3 In terminal, run vcredist_x86.exe with wine
		wine vcredist_x86.exe
	22.4 Done.
22. Office 2007
	22.1 Find Setup.exe (free from Drexel), right click it, Open with Wine Window Program Loader
	22.2 Install winetricks by openning the terminal and type
		sudo wget www.kegel.com/wine/winetricks
	22.3 Install cabextract to extract the contents of Microsoft cabinet archives
		sudo apt-get install cabextract
	22.4 Install the following:
		* corefronts - installs MS Arial, Courier and Times fonts;
		* tahoma - installs tahoma fonts;
		* vcrun2005sp1 - installs MS Visual C++ 2005 sp1 libraries; and
		* wsh56js - installs MS Windows scripting 5.6, jscript only, no script
		code:
		sh winetricks corefonts tahoma vcrun2005sp1 wsh56js
	22.5 Configure wine
		winecfg
		# On the Libraries Tab type ‘riched20’ click add and type ‘usp10’ and click again.
		# Highlight or click 'riched20' and click Edit change it to ‘Native windows’ then click Apply and Ok.

Restart computer

23. Multiple Instances of Totem Movie Player
	23.1 System -> Preferences -> Main Menu
	23.2 Applications -> Sound & Video -> Movie Player -> Properties
	23.3 Change "totem %U" to "totem --no-existing-session"
24. GMP
