		make check
		sudo make install
		(This will be to /usr/local by default)
25. SSH login banner
	25.1 In terminal:
		sudo apt-get install landscape-common
	25.2 Go to /etc/update-motd.d
		sudo chmod 777 00-header
		sudo chmod 777 10-help-text
		sudo chmod 777 20-cpu-checker
		sudo chmod 777 50-landscape-sysinfo
		sudo chmod 777 90-updates-available
	25.3 Use gedit to open 50-landscape-sysinfo, copy the following content
		#!/bin/sh

		echo
		echo -n "  System information as of "
		/bin/date
		echo
		/usr/bin/landscape-sysinfo
	25.4 Use gedit to open 90-updates-available, copy the following content
		#!/bin/sh -e
		#
		# helper for update-motd

		NEED_UPDATE_CHECK=yes

		# check time when we did the last udpate check
		stamp="/var/lib/update-notifier/updates-available"
		if [ -e "$stamp" ]; then
		    stampt=$(stat -c %Y $stamp)
		else
		    stampt=0
		fi

		# output something for update-motd
		if [ -n "$NEED_UPDATE_CHECK" ]; then
		    echo "" > $stamp
		    /usr/lib/update-notifier/apt-check --human-readable >> $stamp
		    echo "" >> $stamp
		fi

		# output what we have (either cached or newly generated)
		cat $stamp
26. Graphite 2.0 alpha 4
	26.1 In terminal:
		sudo apt-get install subversion cmake
		sudo apt-get install python
		sudo apt-get install python-dev
		sudo apt-get install libqt4-dev
		sudo apt-get install libqt4-opengl-dev
		sudo apt-get install libX11-dev
	26.2 Download Graphite-2-a4-src and extract to /home/zexi/Tools/
	26.3 Go to /home/zexi/Tools/Graphite-2-a4-src
		sudo chmod 755 configure.sh
		./configure.sh
	26.4 Go to  build/Linux-Release
		sudo make
	26.5 Graphite's main executable is build/Linux-Release/binaries/bin/graphite
27. QuickSynergy and Synergy (Linux as server, Win 7 as client)
	27.1 Download Synergy at http://synergy-foss.org/pm/projects/synergy/tabs/download
	27.2 In terminal:
		sudo dpkg -i synergy-plus-1.3.4-Linux-x86_64.deb
	27.3 Download QuickSynergy at http://code.google.com/p/quicksynergy/downloads/list
	27.4 In terminal:
		./configure
		make
		make check
		sudo make install
	27.5 QuickSynergy will be install at /usr/local/bin/quicksynergy (create launcher at desktop)
	27.6 Can find a icon for it at /home/zexi/Downloads/quicksynergy-0.9.0/src/logo/qslogo.png
	27.7 Open QuickSynergy, fill in client's ip address at 'Above', 'Left', 'Below', or 'Right'. Click Start.
	27.8 On Windows 7, download Synergy at http://synergy-foss.org/pm/projects/synergy/tabs/download
		install it
		run it as admin
		the screen name for client should be client's ip address





